</head>
<body>
  <h3>Help Page</h3><br>
  <button class="container">About the Generator</button>   <!-- This sections unfold and show the explanation -->
  <div class="content"><p>This <strong>Template generator</strong> will help you establish the very roots of your projects. Create the template you want with your 
    own structure and then download it without typing a single <b>'mkdir'</b> in the terminal. You can also type in the modules you'd like and the generator 
    will include them in the package.json automatically!
  </p></div>
  <button class="container">Usage</button> 
  <div class="content"><p>This page is really easy to use. Click on the button 'generate' to start making your template.
    <br> Name the project and type a little short description for it. <br> The default structure will be shown in the bottom of the page once you click 'generate template'. <br>
    If you'd like to set the folders you want in yor own way just click 'advanced settings' and the options will be shown to you.
  </p></div>
  <button class="container">Who it is aimed for</button> 
  <div class="content"><p>This webpage is aimed for junior programmers, 
    you must have the knowledge about the default structure used in professional world projects.</p>
  </div>
 

 <script>
  var coll = document.getElementsByClassName("container");
  var i;
  for ( i = 0; i < coll.length; i++) {
    coll[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
      this.classList.toggle("active");
      var content = this.nextElementSibling;
      if (content.style.maxHeight){
        content.style.maxHeight = null;
      } else {
        content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + "px";
      } 
    })
  }
</script>
  </body>
</html>